**ScrivenerSync**

Billing Domain Model

Phase 1  |  Version 2

# **1. Purpose and Scope**

This document defines the billing domain model for ScrivenerSync. It specifies the entities, enumerations, business rules, domain services, and invariants required to enforce subscription tier limits, track billing provider state, and route billing events from external providers into the application domain.

Version 2 extends the model to fully specify lapse behaviour: the grace period mechanic, the active-book selection flow, the invisible-development rule for inactive projects, and the immediate publishing restriction that applies on lapse. These rules are designed so that a subscription lapse is invisible to readers for as long as reasonably possible, and the author is never publicly embarrassed by a payment disruption.

The billing system is designed to be backend-agnostic. All interactions with an external billing provider are mediated through an abstract IBillingProvider interface. Two concrete implementations are planned: one targeting Creem and one targeting Paddle. The active provider is selected by configuration at startup; no provider-specific logic appears in the domain or application layers.

Billing entities are intentionally minimal. ScrivenerSync does not store payment card data, process payments, or manage invoices internally. The external provider owns the payment lifecycle. The domain stores only the state required to enforce tier limits and surface subscription status to the author dashboard.

This document is a companion to the ScrivenerSync Business Domain Model. It references entities defined there (Tenancy, Account, ScrivenerProject, TenancyMembership) but does not redefine them.

# **2. Subscription Tiers**

Three tiers are defined. Tier assignment is managed externally by the billing provider via webhook events. The application enforces limits based on the stored tier; it does not communicate with the billing provider at the point of limit enforcement.

| **Tier** | **Beta Readers** | **Active Projects** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Free** | 3 | 1 | Default tier. Assigned on account creation. No payment required. |
| **Paid** | 10 | Unlimited | Activated when provider confirms a paid subscription. |
| **Ultimate** | Unlimited | Unlimited | Activated when provider confirms an Ultimate subscription. |

Unlimited is represented in the domain as a null value on the corresponding limit field, not as a magic integer. Enforcement logic treats null as no ceiling.

# **3. Entities**

## **3.1 SubscriptionRecord**

One record per Tenancy. Holds the canonical subscription state as understood by this application. The external provider is the source of truth for payment status; this record reflects the most recent provider-confirmed state.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. One-to-one. |
| **Tier** | Enumeration: Free, Paid, Ultimate. The currently active tier. |
| **Status** | Enumeration: Active, PastDue, Cancelled, Trialing, Paused. Mirrors the provider lifecycle state. |
| **ProviderName** | Enumeration: Creem, Paddle. Identifies which billing provider is managing this subscription. Null for Free tier accounts with no provider record. |
| **ProviderSubscriptionId** | The subscription identifier assigned by the external provider. Null for Free tier accounts. Used to correlate incoming webhook events. |
| **ProviderCustomerId** | The customer identifier assigned by the external provider. Null for Free tier accounts. Stable across subscription changes. |
| **CurrentPeriodStart** | Timestamp. Start of the current billing period. Null for Free tier. |
| **CurrentPeriodEnd** | Timestamp. End of the current billing period. Null for Free tier. Used to detect lapsed subscriptions if webhooks are missed. |
| **CancelAtPeriodEnd** | Boolean. True when the author has requested cancellation but the subscription remains active until the current period ends. |
| **LapsedAt** | Timestamp. Set when Status first transitions to PastDue or Cancelled from a previously paid tier. Null if never lapsed. This is the anchor for all grace period calculations. |
| **TrialEndsAt** | Timestamp. Populated during a trial period. Null otherwise. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of record creation. |
| **UpdatedAt** | Timestamp of most recent update. Set on every webhook-driven state change. |

## **3.2 LapseGracePeriod**

Tracks the author's active-book selection deferral state during a subscription lapse. One record per lapse event. Created when a paid subscription first enters a lapsed state (PastDue or Cancelled). Closed when the author makes their active-book selection, or when the subscription is restored.

The grace period has two phases. During the first 14 days after lapse, the author may dismiss the active-book selection prompt any number of times. After 14 days, one final dismissal is permitted before the prompt becomes a non-dismissable blocking gate.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. One-to-one per lapse event. |
| **SubscriptionRecordId** | Foreign key to SubscriptionRecord. |
| **GraceStartedAt** | Timestamp. Set to the value of SubscriptionRecord.LapsedAt when the record is created. |
| **GraceEndsAt** | Timestamp. GraceStartedAt plus 14 days. After this point the post-grace dismissal allowance applies. |
| **PostGraceDismissalsUsed** | Integer. Number of dismissals used after GraceEndsAt. Maximum value of 1. Once this reaches 1 the prompt is non-dismissable. |
| **SelectionMade** | Boolean. True when the author has completed the active-book selection. False while deferring. |
| **SelectionMadeAt** | Timestamp. Set when SelectionMade transitions to true. Null until then. |
| **SelectedProjectId** | Foreign key to ScrivenerProject. The project the author chose as their single active project. Null until selection is made. |
| **ClosedAt** | Timestamp. Set when the grace period record is closed, either by the author making their selection or by the subscription being restored. Null while open. |
| **ClosureReason** | Enumeration: SelectionMade, SubscriptionRestored. Null while open. |

## **3.3 BillingWebhookEvent**

A log of every inbound webhook payload received from the billing provider. Stored before processing to support idempotency, replay, and audit. Processing outcome is recorded after the event is handled.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **ProviderName** | Enumeration: Creem, Paddle. The provider that sent this event. |
| **ProviderEventId** | The event identifier assigned by the provider. Used for idempotency — duplicate provider event IDs are detected and skipped. |
| **EventType** | The raw event type string as received from the provider (e.g. subscription.activated, subscription.cancelled). Stored verbatim. |
| **Payload** | The full JSON payload as received. Stored verbatim for replay capability. |
| **ReceivedAt** | Timestamp of receipt by the webhook endpoint. |
| **ProcessedAt** | Timestamp of successful processing. Null if unprocessed or failed. |
| **ProcessingStatus** | Enumeration: Pending, Processed, Failed, Skipped. Skipped is used for duplicate or unrecognised event types. |
| **FailureReason** | Free text. Populated if ProcessingStatus is Failed. Null otherwise. |
| **AttemptCount** | Integer. Number of processing attempts made. Minimum 1 after first attempt. |

## **3.4 TierLimitSnapshot**

A point-in-time record of the limits enforced at each tier, stored alongside the tier assignment. Allows the application to reconstruct what limits applied at any historical point without depending on current configuration. Created whenever a tier change occurs.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **SubscriptionRecordId** | Foreign key to SubscriptionRecord. |
| **Tier** | The tier these limits correspond to. |
| **MaxBetaReaders** | Integer. The maximum number of active beta readers permitted. Null means unlimited. |
| **MaxActiveProjects** | Integer. The maximum number of reader-active projects permitted simultaneously. Null means unlimited. |
| **EffectiveFrom** | Timestamp. When this snapshot became the active limit set. |
| **EffectiveTo** | Timestamp. When this snapshot was superseded by a newer one. Null if currently active. |

# **4. Enumerations**

| **Enumeration** | **Value** | **Meaning** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Tier** | Free | Default tier. No payment required. | Assigned at account creation. |
|  | Paid | Paid subscription. Up to 10 readers. |  |
|  | Ultimate | Premium subscription. Unlimited readers. |  |
| **SubscriptionStatus** | Active | Subscription is current and paid. | Normal operating state. |
|  | PastDue | Payment failed; grace period applies. | Access not immediately revoked. |
|  | Cancelled | Subscription cancelled. Access ends at period end if CancelAtPeriodEnd, else immediately. |  |
|  | Trialing | Within a free trial window. | Tier limits of the trialled plan apply. |
|  | Paused | Subscription paused by the author. | Provider-dependent. |
| **ProviderName** | Creem | Creem billing provider. | Preferred at launch. 0% fee up to €1,000 MRR. |
|  | Paddle | Paddle billing provider. | Alternative. 5% + $0.50 per transaction. |
| **WebhookProcessingStatus** | Pending | Received, not yet processed. |  |
|  | Processed | Event handled successfully. |  |
|  | Failed | Processing failed after all retry attempts. |  |
|  | Skipped | Duplicate event ID or unrecognised event type. |  |
| **GracePeriodClosureReason** | SelectionMade | Author completed the active-book selection. | Normal closure path. |
|  | SubscriptionRestored | Payment resolved before selection was required. | Grace period closed without the author needing to select. |

# **5. Lapse Behaviour**

This section defines what happens when a paid subscription lapses, either through non-payment (PastDue) or explicit cancellation (Cancelled). The overriding design principle is that a lapse should be invisible to readers for as long as reasonably possible. From a reader's perspective, an author who has lapsed looks identical to an author who is simply not publishing new material.

## **5.1 Immediate Restrictions on Lapse**

The following restrictions take effect the moment LapsedAt is set, regardless of the grace period state:

- No new invitations may be issued to beta readers.

- No new sections may be published on any project.

- No new projects may be activated for readers.

These restrictions are enforced silently from the author's perspective — the capability is simply unavailable in the UI. No error messaging is shown to readers.

## **5.2 What Is Preserved on Lapse**

The following capabilities are fully preserved throughout the grace period and beyond, regardless of whether the author has made their active-book selection:

- All projects remain visible to all readers exactly as before.

- All previously published sections remain readable.

- All existing comment threads remain accessible and threadable by readers.

- The author may continue to respond to comments on any project.

- Reading progress tracking continues normally.

- The sync process continues to run, keeping section content current with the Scrivener source. The author may write freely in Scrivener; the content updates in the system. The content simply cannot be published until the lapse is resolved or an active book is selected.

## **5.3 The Grace Period**

A LapseGracePeriod record is created when the subscription first enters a lapsed state. The grace period has two phases:

### **Phase 1 — First 14 Days (Free Deferral)**

During the first 14 days after LapsedAt, the author sees a dismissable prompt on login inviting them to select their active book. They may dismiss this prompt any number of times. The system continues in its full pre-lapse visible state throughout this phase.

### **Phase 2 — After 14 Days (One Final Deferral)**

After 14 days, the author is permitted exactly one further dismissal (PostGraceDismissalsUsed ≤ 1). Once that dismissal is used, or if they did not dismiss in Phase 1, the prompt becomes a non-dismissable blocking gate on the next login. The author must complete the active-book selection before accessing any other part of the application.

The intent of the two-phase design is that accidental lapses — failed card renewal, bank hold, brief oversight — typically resolve within 14 days without the author ever needing to act. The post-grace allowance provides a final buffer for authors who are aware of the lapse but have not yet decided which book to prioritise.

## **5.4 The Active-Book Selection**

The active-book selection may be initiated by the author at any time during the grace period — they do not need to wait for the prompt to become mandatory. If the author needs to publish during the grace period, they simply complete the selection early, which immediately restores publishing capability on the chosen project.

The selection process requires the author to:

- Choose one ScrivenerProject to remain reader-active. All other projects are deactivated for readers.

- Choose which beta readers remain active on that project, within the Free tier limit of 3. Other readers’ memberships are deactivated (IsActive = false) but not deleted.

Once the selection is made:

- The chosen project immediately regains full publishing capability.

- Deactivated readers are notified on their next login that they cannot currently make comments, but may still read all previously published content on all projects.

- No data is removed. Deactivated readers retain all their comment history and reading progress.

- LapseGracePeriod.SelectionMade is set true and SelectionMadeAt is recorded.

## **5.5 Invisible Development on Inactive Projects**

After the active-book selection is made, all projects other than the selected one become inactive. The following rules apply to those inactive projects:

- The author may continue writing in Scrivener normally. The sync process runs and content updates are tracked in the system.

- No new sections may be published on inactive projects.

- If the project has prior reader activity (at least one ReadEvent or Comment exists on any of its sections), the project and its published sections remain visible to readers in a static read-only state.

- If the project has no prior reader activity — it is a work in development that readers have never seen — the project becomes invisible to all readers. The author may prepare and develop it freely without it appearing on any reader’s dashboard.

- When the subscription is restored, invisible projects immediately become visible again and the author may publish from them.

This rule allows the lapsed author to use the inactive period productively: writing new material in private, ready to publish the moment their subscription resumes.

## **5.6 Subscription Restoration**

If the subscription is restored at any point — payment resolved, new subscription activated — the following occurs immediately:

- All publishing, invitation, and project activation capabilities are restored.

- Any open LapseGracePeriod record is closed with ClosureReason = SubscriptionRestored.

- If the author had already completed the active-book selection, their chosen configuration remains in place. They must manually reactivate other projects and readers if they wish to.

- If the author had not yet completed the selection, no selection is required. The system returns to its full pre-lapse state.

- Invisible inactive projects immediately become visible to readers again.

- The grace period dismiss count and deadline are reset. A new lapse, if it occurs, starts a fresh LapseGracePeriod record.

# **6. Provider Abstraction**

All billing provider interactions are routed through IBillingProvider. The domain and application layers depend only on this interface. Concrete implementations (CreemBillingProvider, PaddleBillingProvider) are registered in the dependency injection container by configuration and are never referenced directly in business logic.

The interface defines the following operations:

| **Method** | **Signature (conceptual)** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **CreateCheckoutSession** | CreateCheckoutSession(tier, authorEmail) → CheckoutUrl | Generates a provider-hosted checkout URL for the given tier. The author is redirected here to enter payment details. The provider handles the checkout UI entirely. |
| **CreateCustomerPortalSession** | CreateCustomerPortalSession(providerCustomerId) → PortalUrl | Generates a provider-hosted URL for the author to manage their subscription: update payment method, cancel, view invoices. |
| **GetSubscriptionState** | GetSubscriptionState(providerSubscriptionId) → ProviderSubscriptionDto | Fetches the current subscription state directly from the provider. Used for reconciliation if a webhook is missed. |
| **ValidateWebhookSignature** | ValidateWebhookSignature(payload, signature, secret) → bool | Verifies that an inbound webhook payload was signed by the provider using the configured webhook secret. Must be called before processing any webhook event. |
| **MapEventToCommand** | MapEventToCommand(providerEventType, payload) → IBillingCommand? | Translates a raw provider event type and payload into a provider-agnostic domain command. Returns null for unrecognised or irrelevant event types. |
| **GetProviderName** | GetProviderName() → ProviderName | Returns the ProviderName enumeration value for the active implementation. Used when persisting BillingWebhookEvent records. |

Provider-specific concepts — such as Creem’s product IDs, Paddle’s price IDs, or event type naming conventions — are confined entirely to the concrete implementation classes and their configuration. They do not appear in domain entities, commands, or application services.

# **7. Business Rules**

## **7.1 Provider Independence**

- The active billing provider is selected by configuration at startup. Switching providers requires a configuration change and a new concrete IBillingProvider implementation; no domain or application code changes.

- No provider SDK, HTTP client, or provider-specific type is referenced outside the billing infrastructure layer.

- Webhook signature validation is mandatory. Any inbound webhook that fails signature validation is rejected with HTTP 400 and logged but not persisted as a BillingWebhookEvent.

## **7.2 Tier Enforcement**

- Tier limits are enforced at the point of the action that would exceed them: inviting a beta reader, and activating a project for readers.

- The enforcement check reads MaxBetaReaders and MaxActiveProjects from the currently active TierLimitSnapshot. It does not call the billing provider at enforcement time.

- A null limit value means the action is always permitted regardless of current count.

- When CancelAtPeriodEnd is true, the subscription remains Active with full tier privileges until CurrentPeriodEnd. The tier is downgraded only when the period ends and a cancellation webhook is received and processed.

- PastDue subscriptions retain their tier privileges during the grace period. The grace period duration is governed by LapseGracePeriod, not by the billing provider.

## **7.3 Webhook Processing**

- Every inbound webhook is persisted as a BillingWebhookEvent with ProcessingStatus = Pending before any processing logic is invoked.

- If a BillingWebhookEvent with the same ProviderEventId already exists, the new event is persisted with ProcessingStatus = Skipped and processing is not attempted. This is the idempotency guarantee.

- MapEventToCommand translates the raw event into a domain command. If no mapping exists the event is marked Skipped.

- If command execution fails, the event is marked Failed and AttemptCount is incremented. A background retry job reattempts Failed events up to a configured maximum.

- After the maximum retry attempts are exhausted, the event remains Failed and is surfaced on the author dashboard as a billing alert.

- Webhook endpoints are provider-specific URL paths (e.g. /webhooks/creem, /webhooks/paddle). Each path is registered only when its corresponding provider is active.

## **7.4 Free Tier Behaviour**

- All new author accounts are created with Tier = Free, Status = Active, and no ProviderName, ProviderSubscriptionId, or ProviderCustomerId.

- Free tier accounts are not subject to the lapse mechanic. LapseGracePeriod records are never created for Free tier accounts. The Free tier limits apply permanently without a grace period.

- A Free tier account that has never interacted with a provider has a null ProviderName. This is valid and must not be treated as an error.

## **7.5 Tier Change Rules**

- A TierLimitSnapshot is created whenever Tier changes on a SubscriptionRecord. The previous snapshot’s EffectiveTo is set to the current timestamp.

- Tier changes are always driven by processed webhook events. The application never changes Tier directly in response to a user action.

- An upgrade (Free → Paid, Free → Ultimate, Paid → Ultimate) takes effect immediately when the corresponding activation event is processed.

- A downgrade (Ultimate → Paid, Paid → Free) takes effect when the cancellation or downgrade event is processed, which may be at the end of the billing period if CancelAtPeriodEnd was true.

## **7.6 Lapse Grace Period Rules**

- A LapseGracePeriod record is created the first time SubscriptionRecord.Status transitions to PastDue or Cancelled from a previously paid tier (Paid or Ultimate). LapsedAt is set on the SubscriptionRecord at the same time.

- Only one LapseGracePeriod record may be open (ClosedAt = null) per Tenancy at any time.

- During the 14-day grace phase (current timestamp ≤ GraceEndsAt), the author may dismiss the active-book selection prompt any number of times with no constraint.

- After the grace phase (current timestamp > GraceEndsAt), the author may dismiss the prompt exactly once (PostGraceDismissalsUsed = 1). Recording a dismissal after GraceEndsAt increments PostGraceDismissalsUsed and must be rejected if it would exceed 1.

- Once PostGraceDismissalsUsed = 1 and GraceEndsAt has passed, the active-book selection prompt is non-dismissable. It is rendered as a blocking gate and no other part of the application is accessible until the selection is made.

- The author may voluntarily make the active-book selection at any time during the grace period, including during Phase 1. Early selection is not penalised.

- Making the active-book selection sets SelectionMade = true, records SelectionMadeAt, records SelectedProjectId, and closes the LapseGracePeriod with ClosureReason = SelectionMade.

- When the subscription is restored, any open LapseGracePeriod record is closed with ClosureReason = SubscriptionRestored, LapsedAt on the SubscriptionRecord is cleared, and PostGraceDismissalsUsed is not carried forward to any future lapse.

## **7.7 Invisible Development Rules**

- A ScrivenerProject on a lapsed Tenancy, or on a Tenancy that has made the active-book selection and not chosen this project, is considered an inactive project.

- An inactive project with no prior reader activity (zero ReadEvents and zero Comments on any of its sections) is invisible to all readers. It does not appear on any reader dashboard or project list.

- An inactive project with prior reader activity remains visible to readers in a fully static read-only state: all previously published sections are readable, all existing comments are visible, but no new sections may be published.

- The sync process continues to run on all inactive projects regardless of visibility. Content updates are tracked internally. The author may write freely in Scrivener.

- When the subscription is restored, all invisible projects immediately become visible to readers and publishing capability is restored.

## **7.8 Reader Notification on Lapse**

- Readers whose memberships have been deactivated as a result of the active-book selection are notified on their next login that they cannot currently make comments.

- The notification does not reference billing, subscription status, or any payment-related reason. The messaging is neutral.

- Deactivated readers may still read all previously published sections on all projects that have prior reader activity.

- No notification is sent to readers during the grace period, before the active-book selection is made. From a reader’s perspective, nothing has changed.

## **7.9 Publishing During Lapse**

- Publishing is blocked on all projects from the moment LapsedAt is set.

- If the author wishes to publish during the lapse, they must first complete the active-book selection. Once the selection is made, publishing capability is immediately restored on the chosen project only.

- Completing the selection early to unblock publishing does not change the grace period timeline. The LapseGracePeriod record is closed with ClosureReason = SelectionMade regardless of when the selection occurs.

# **8. Domain Services**

## **8.1 BillingProviderService**

Wraps IBillingProvider. Orchestrates checkout and portal session creation.

| **Operation** | **Description** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **StartUpgradeCheckout(tier, tenancyId)** | Validates the tenancy and the requested tier is a valid upgrade. Calls IBillingProvider.CreateCheckoutSession. Returns the checkout URL. | Does not modify SubscriptionRecord. Tier change happens when the provider sends a confirmation webhook. |
| **StartCustomerPortalSession(tenancyId)** | Looks up the ProviderCustomerId from SubscriptionRecord. Calls IBillingProvider.CreateCustomerPortalSession. Returns the portal URL. | Fails if ProviderCustomerId is null (Free tier with no prior provider interaction). |
| **ReconcileSubscription(tenancyId)** | Calls IBillingProvider.GetSubscriptionState. If the returned state differs from the stored SubscriptionRecord, applies the difference as if a webhook had been received. | Used by a scheduled job to recover from missed webhooks. |

## **8.2 WebhookIngestionService**

Called by the provider-specific webhook controller. Handles receipt, signature validation, persistence, and dispatch.

| **Operation** | **Description** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **IngestWebhook(providerName, payload, signature)** | Validates the signature via IBillingProvider.ValidateWebhookSignature. Persists a BillingWebhookEvent. Returns the event ID. | HTTP 400 returned to caller if signature fails. Event not persisted on signature failure. |
| **ProcessWebhookEvent(eventId)** | Loads the BillingWebhookEvent. Checks for duplicate ProviderEventId. Calls IBillingProvider.MapEventToCommand. Executes the resulting command via SubscriptionUpdateService. Updates ProcessingStatus. | Idempotent. Safe to call multiple times on the same event. |
| **RetryFailedEvents()** | Finds all BillingWebhookEvent records with ProcessingStatus = Failed and AttemptCount below the retry ceiling. Calls ProcessWebhookEvent for each. | Run by a background job on a configured schedule. |

## **8.3 SubscriptionUpdateService**

Applies the outcome of a processed billing event to the domain. The single point at which SubscriptionRecord is mutated in response to provider events.

| **Operation** | **Description** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **ActivateSubscription(cmd)** | Sets Tier, Status = Active, ProviderName, ProviderSubscriptionId, ProviderCustomerId, CurrentPeriodStart, CurrentPeriodEnd. Creates a TierLimitSnapshot. If a LapseGracePeriod is open, closes it with ClosureReason = SubscriptionRestored and clears LapsedAt. | Handles new subscriptions and reactivations after lapse. |
| **UpdateSubscriptionPeriod(cmd)** | Updates CurrentPeriodStart, CurrentPeriodEnd on renewal. No tier change. | Triggered by renewal events. |
| **SetPastDue(cmd)** | Sets Status = PastDue. Sets LapsedAt if not already set. Creates a LapseGracePeriod record if none is open. Does not change Tier. |  |
| **SetCancelAtPeriodEnd(cmd)** | Sets CancelAtPeriodEnd = true. Status remains Active. | Triggered when the author cancels but the period has not ended. |
| **CancelSubscription(cmd)** | Sets Status = Cancelled, Tier = Free. Sets LapsedAt if not already set. Creates a LapseGracePeriod record if none is open. Creates a TierLimitSnapshot for Free. | Triggered at period end, or immediately if CancelAtPeriodEnd was false. |
| **PauseSubscription(cmd)** | Sets Status = Paused. Tier is retained. Does not trigger a lapse. | Provider-dependent capability. |
| **ResumeSubscription(cmd)** | Sets Status = Active. Tier is retained. |  |

## **8.4 LapseGracePeriodService**

Manages the active-book selection deferral mechanic. Called on every author login when a LapseGracePeriod record is open.

| **Operation** | **Description** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **GetGraceState(tenancyId)** | Returns the open LapseGracePeriod record for the Tenancy, or null if none exists. Returns the current phase (WithinGrace, PostGrace), the remaining dismissals, and whether the prompt is currently blocking. | Called on author login. |
| **RecordDismissal(tenancyId)** | Validates a dismissal is permitted. If within the 14-day grace phase, records no persistent state (dismissals in this phase are uncounted). If post-grace, increments PostGraceDismissalsUsed. Rejects the dismissal if PostGraceDismissalsUsed would exceed 1. |  |
| **CompleteSelection(tenancyId, projectId, activeReaderAccountIds)** | Validates the project belongs to the Tenancy. Deactivates all other projects. Deactivates all reader memberships not in activeReaderAccountIds, within Free tier limits. Sets SelectionMade = true, SelectionMadeAt, SelectedProjectId. Closes the LapseGracePeriod with ClosureReason = SelectionMade. Queues deactivated-reader notifications. | May be called at any time during the grace period, including Phase 1. |
| **IsPublishingBlocked(tenancyId)** | Returns true if a LapseGracePeriod is open and SelectionMade = false. | Called before any publish action. |

## **8.5 TierEnforcementService**

Called by the application layer before operations that are subject to tier limits. Reads only from domain state; never calls the billing provider.

| **Operation** | **Description** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **CanInviteReader(tenancyId)** | Returns true if the current active reader count is below MaxBetaReaders (or MaxBetaReaders is null), and the subscription is not in a lapsed state. |  |
| **CanActivateProject(tenancyId)** | Returns true if the count of reader-active projects is below MaxActiveProjects (or MaxActiveProjects is null), and the subscription is not in a lapsed state. |  |
| **CanPublish(tenancyId)** | Returns true if the subscription is not lapsed, or if lapsed and SelectionMade = true for the target project. | Delegates to LapseGracePeriodService.IsPublishingBlocked. |
| **GetCurrentLimits(tenancyId)** | Returns the active TierLimitSnapshot for the Tenancy. | Used by the dashboard to display current plan limits. |
| **IsOverLimit(tenancyId)** | Returns true if either reader count exceeds MaxBetaReaders or active project count exceeds MaxActiveProjects. |  |
| **GetOverLimitDetails(tenancyId)** | Returns a description of which limits are exceeded and by how much. | Used to populate the dashboard warning. |

# **9. Invariants**

The following conditions must hold at all times. Any operation that would violate an invariant must be rejected before persistence.

| **Invariant** | **Statement** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **B-01** | Exactly one SubscriptionRecord exists per Tenancy. |  |
| **B-02** | SubscriptionRecord.ProviderName is null if and only if ProviderSubscriptionId and ProviderCustomerId are also null. | Free tier accounts with no provider history have all three null. |
| **B-03** | A BillingWebhookEvent with ProcessingStatus = Processed must have a non-null ProcessedAt timestamp. |  |
| **B-04** | A BillingWebhookEvent with ProcessingStatus = Pending or Skipped must have a null ProcessedAt timestamp. |  |
| **B-05** | No two BillingWebhookEvent records for the same ProviderName may share the same ProviderEventId, unless one is Skipped. | Idempotency constraint. |
| **B-06** | At most one TierLimitSnapshot per SubscriptionRecord has a null EffectiveTo at any time. | The active snapshot. |
| **B-07** | TierLimitSnapshot.EffectiveFrom is immutable after creation. |  |
| **B-08** | SubscriptionRecord.Tier = Free implies Status = Active or Status = Cancelled. | Free tier is never PastDue, Trialing, or Paused. |
| **B-09** | CancelAtPeriodEnd = true implies Status = Active. | A cancelled-at-period-end subscription is still Active until the period ends. |
| **B-10** | SubscriptionRecord.CurrentPeriodEnd is null if and only if Tier = Free and ProviderSubscriptionId is null. |  |
| **B-11** | BillingWebhookEvent.AttemptCount is >= 1 for any record with ProcessingStatus other than Pending. |  |
| **B-12** | At most one LapseGracePeriod per Tenancy may have ClosedAt = null at any time. | Only one open grace period per Tenancy. |
| **B-13** | LapseGracePeriod.GraceEndsAt must equal GraceStartedAt plus exactly 14 days. |  |
| **B-14** | LapseGracePeriod.PostGraceDismissalsUsed must not exceed 1. |  |
| **B-15** | LapseGracePeriod.SelectionMade = true implies SelectionMadeAt and SelectedProjectId are non-null. |  |
| **B-16** | LapseGracePeriod.ClosedAt is non-null if and only if ClosureReason is non-null. |  |
| **B-17** | A LapseGracePeriod record may only exist for a Tenancy whose SubscriptionRecord.LapsedAt is non-null. |  |
| **B-18** | SubscriptionRecord.LapsedAt is null for any Tenancy with Tier = Free and no prior paid subscription. |  |
| **B-19** | PostGraceDismissalsUsed may only be incremented when the current timestamp is greater than GraceEndsAt. | Dismissals during the 14-day phase are uncounted. |
| **B-20** | LapseGracePeriod.SelectedProjectId must reference a ScrivenerProject belonging to the same Tenancy. |  |

# **10. Provider Implementation Notes**

This section documents the provider-specific mapping details required by each concrete IBillingProvider implementation. This information is confined to the infrastructure layer.

## **10.1 Creem**

Creem is the preferred launch provider. At launch, Creem charges 0% on the first €1,000 of monthly revenue, making it the lowest-cost option at early scale.

| **IBillingProvider method** | **Creem mechanism** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **CreateCheckoutSession** | Creem hosted checkout link with product_id parameter. | Product IDs for Paid and Ultimate tiers are configured via environment variables. Checkout link includes a redirect URL and a client_reference_id set to the Tenancy owner’s AccountId. |
| **CreateCustomerPortalSession** | Creem customer portal link. | Requires ProviderCustomerId. Creem assigns this when the first subscription is created. |
| **GetSubscriptionState** | Creem GET /subscriptions/{id} API endpoint. | Used for reconciliation. |
| **ValidateWebhookSignature** | HMAC-SHA256 signature validation against Creem-Webhook-Signature header. | Secret configured per environment. |
| **MapEventToCommand** | subscription.active → ActivateSubscriptionCommand. subscription.cancelled → CancelSubscriptionCommand. subscription.updated → UpdateSubscriptionPeriodCommand. subscription.past_due → SetPastDueCommand. | Event type strings are Creem-specific. Mapping is internal to CreemBillingProvider. |

## **10.2 Paddle**

Paddle is the secondary provider. It acts as Merchant of Record, handling global VAT and tax compliance. Fee is 5% + $0.50 per transaction. A configuration change and a PaddleBillingProvider implementation are the only requirements to switch from Creem.

| **IBillingProvider method** | **Paddle mechanism** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **CreateCheckoutSession** | Paddle.js overlay or hosted checkout with price_id parameter. | Price IDs for Paid and Ultimate tiers configured via environment variables. |
| **CreateCustomerPortalSession** | Paddle customer portal URL. | Paddle assigns customer_id on first transaction. |
| **GetSubscriptionState** | Paddle GET /subscriptions/{id} API. |  |
| **ValidateWebhookSignature** | Paddle-Signature header verification using HMAC-SHA256. | Paddle sends notification_id in the payload usable as ProviderEventId. |
| **MapEventToCommand** | subscription.activated → ActivateSubscriptionCommand. subscription.cancelled → CancelSubscriptionCommand. subscription.updated → UpdateSubscriptionPeriodCommand. subscription.past_due → SetPastDueCommand. subscription.paused → PauseSubscriptionCommand. subscription.resumed → ResumeSubscriptionCommand. | Paddle exposes more lifecycle events than Creem. Extra events map to commands not reachable via Creem. |

# **11. Deferred and Out of Scope**

- Billing UI within the application. Checkout and customer portal are provider-hosted. The application issues redirect URLs only.

- Invoice storage. Invoices are owned and displayed by the provider.

- Refund processing. Refunds are initiated via the provider’s dashboard or portal.

- Per-reader or per-project billing. All current tiers are flat-rate subscriptions.

- Proration on mid-cycle tier changes. Provider handles proration; the domain responds to the resulting events.

- Multi-currency display. The provider handles currency and localisation at checkout.

- Affiliate or referral tracking. Not in scope for Phase 1.

- Admin interface for tier management. Tier assignment is provider-driven via webhooks; manual overrides are out of scope.

- Configurable grace period duration. The 14-day window is fixed in Phase 1. Making it configurable per-tier or per-provider is deferred.